AC   Q9HY63;
Bifunctional polymyxin resistance arnA protein [Includes: UDP-
glucuronic acid decarboxylase (EC 4.1.1.-) (UDP-GlcUA decarboxylase)
(ArnAFT); UDP-4-amino-4-deoxy-L-arabinose formyltransferase
(EC 2.1.2.-) (UDP-L-Ara4N formyltransferase) (ArnADH)].
"Complete genome sequence of Pseudomonas aeruginosa PAO1, an
opportunistic pathogen.";
-!- FUNCTION: Bifunctional enzyme that catalyzes the decarboxylation
    of UDP-glucuronic acid (UDP-GlcA) to UDP-4-keto-arabinose (UDP-
    Ara4O) and the addition of a formyl group to UDP-4-amino-4-deoxy-
    L-arabinose (UDP-L-Ara4N) to form UDP-L-4-formamido-arabinose
    (UDP-L-Ara4FN). The modified arabinose is attached to lipid A and
    is required for resistance to polymyxin and cationic antimicrobial
    peptides (By similarity).
-!- CATALYTIC ACTIVITY: UDP-glucuronic acid + NAD(+) = UDP-beta-(L-
    threo-pentapyranosyl-4''-ulose) + CO(2) + NADH.
-!- CATALYTIC ACTIVITY: 10-formyltetrahydrofolate + UDP-4-amino-4-
    deoxy-L-arabinose = tetrahydrofolate + UDP-beta-(4-deoxy-4-
    formamido-L-arabinose).
-!- PATHWAY: Lipid A modification with 4-amino-4-deoxy-L-arabinose;
    step 2.
-!- PATHWAY: Lipid A modification with 4-amino-4-deoxy-L-arabinose;
    step 4.
-!- SIMILARITY: In the N-terminal section; belongs to the fmt family.
    UDP-L-Ara4N formyltransferase subfamily.
-!- SIMILARITY: In the C-terminal section; belongs to the sugar
    epimerase family. UDP-glucuronic acid decarboxylase subfamily.
 GO:0016831; F:carboxy-lyase activity; IEA:HAMAP.
